1. Frontend

The frontend is for guests, staff, and admins to interact with the system.

Core Features

Guest Portal

View available rooms

Search & filter rooms by type, price, amenities

Make reservations

View booking history

Payment for bookings

Staff Portal

Check-in / Check-out guests

Manage room availability and cleaning status

Manage guest requests

Admin Panel

Add/edit/delete rooms

View reservations and revenue reports

Manage staff accounts

Notifications

Email/SMS for booking confirmations and reminders

Tech Stack

React.js / Next.js 

Tailwind CSS / Material UI

State management: Redux / Context API

HTTP requests: Axios / Fetch API

Routing: React Router / Next.js routing

2. Backend 

Backend manages booking logic, payments, user management, and reporting.

Core Features

User Management

Guest and staff accounts

Authentication (JWT)

Room Management

CRUD operations for rooms

Track availability, status (cleaning, occupied, vacant)

Booking Management

Reservation creation, modification, cancellation

Check-in / Check-out updates

Payment Processing

Integrate Stripe / PayPal

Record payment status

Reporting

Revenue, occupancy rate, guest activity

Notifications

Send booking confirmation / reminders

Security

Role-based access: guest, staff, admin

Input validation

Tech Stack

Node.js + Express (or Django/Flask)

REST API or GraphQL

Authentication: JWT

File uploads: Multer (for room images)

3. Database Layer

Database stores rooms, bookings, users, payments, and logs.

Essential Tables/Collections

Users

Name, email, password, role (guest/staff/admin), contact info

Rooms

Number, type, price, status (vacant/occupied), amenities, images

Bookings

User ID, room ID, check-in/out dates, status, total price

Payments

Booking ID, payment method, amount, status

Staff Tasks / Logs

Room cleaning, maintenance requests

Reviews / Feedback

Guest reviews for rooms or services

Tech Stack

SQL: MySQL, PostgreSQL

NoSQL: MongoDB

Optional caching: Redis (for sessions, availability checks)

4. Additional Requirements

Environment & Config

.env file for API keys, DB connections, secret keys

Deployment

Frontend: Vercel, Netlify

Backend: Heroku, AWS, Render

Database: MongoDB Atlas / RDS / PostgreSQL

Security

HTTPS/SSL

Role-based access control

Input validation and sanitization

Testing

Unit tests, integration tests (Jest, Mocha)

Third-Party Services

Payment gateways (Stripe, PayPal)

Cloud storage for room images (AWS S3 / Cloudinary)

Flow Diagram (Text Version)
[Guest / Staff / Admin Browser or Mobile App]
                  |
                  v
           [Frontend (React/Next.js)]
                  |
           HTTP Requests / REST API
                  |
                  v
             [Backend (Node.js/Express)]
                  |
   ----------------------------------------
   |           |           |              |
   v           v           v              v
[Auth]     [Rooms]    [Bookings]    [Payments]
                  |
                  v
              [Database]
                  |
                  v
         [Third-Party Services]
  (Payment gateway, Cloud Storage)


